Shane's Foods

Tomato and Broccoli soup
- Canned tomatos
- Head of broccoli (1 head per can)
- Dried chilli flakes
- Rosemary? (not confident in this, but spice to taste)
- Salt to taste
- Chicken broth/ stock

Sourdough naan bread
- 50% flour 
- 50% water
- Olive Oil
- Salt
- flatten with hand
- Cool in skilet with oil


Sourdough bread
- 0-12h Leaven: Mix tablespoon of starter with even weight parts water and flour.
- 12-13h Disolve 1 tablespoon of salt into half of the final about of water to be used
- 12-15h Autolyse : Mix Leaven with 1:5 water. Once the Leaven is broken up into the water, add the flower 1:1 with water and mix till smooth. 
- 15-17h Folding: Add salt water and fold the dough over itself to create the network of gluten holes, letting the dough sit in between folding sessions.
- 17-20h Proofing: Shaping the dough in a bowl lined with cloth that is covered in flour.
- 20-21.5h Cooking: Preheat oven to 475F - 500F and bake bread for 1 - 1.5 hours. *If possible, steam helps to keep the break moist and springy.


Manchurian Gravy/ Sauce
- Olive Oil
- Garlic
- Green Chillies
- Green Onions
- Green peppers
- Corn flour and water (1:2 ratio)
- Soy Sauce
- Salt & suger (To taste)
- Chilli garlic sauce

Directions
1. Finely dice everything.
2. Mess it up in a pan with oil

Pakora
- Onion
- Garlic
- Cauliflower
- Flour (chickpea)

Directions
1. Combine spices in bowl and add water to make batter
2. Put cauliflower, onion and other veggies in batter
3. Fry in oil

Ginger Beef Sauce
- 2 Tbsp unseasoned rice vinegar
- 5 Tbsp soy sauce (use gluten-free soy sauce if cooking gluten-free)
- 1 Tbsp honey
- 1 Tbsp peeled, grated fresh ginger
- 1 teaspoon chile pepper flakes
- 1 teaspoon ground cumin